        {
            "heading": "Introduction",
            "content": [
                "Polish nouns, pronouns, adjectives, numbers, and possessives change depending on the case.",
                "There are 7 cases: Nominative, Genitive, Dative, Accusative, Instrumental, Locative, and Vocative.",
                "Cases indicate the grammatical role of a word in a sentence.",
                "In this lesson, you'll learn the main uses of cases with examples and references to full declension tables."
            ]
        },
        {
